<dl id="n34031d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n34" href="#n34031d">N34 (VI.B.27)</a>:  <a href="../../ff/fnbs/n34all.htm#n34031d"> 31(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> <font face="wake">G</font> vary directly <small>Blue</small></blockquote> <dd class="well"> <ul class="list-inline" id="n34031d"><li>FW 252.16 </li><li><a href="../../flex/kf/lexkf.htm#n34031d">2010</a> </li><li><a href="../../flex/kf/l39kf.htm#n34031d">1939</a> </li><li><ms href="#n34031d">MS missing</ms> </li><li>JJA not reproduced <a name="kfad1" href="../../ff/fdra/kda.htm#kfCFd1">Usage</a> </li><li> <a href="../../flex/kf/kfd1.htm#n34031d">Draft: II.1&sect;6CF.1</a></li> </ul> <blockquote class="sources">Definition. One quantity A is said to <b>vary directly</b> as another B, when the two quantities depend upon each other in such a manner that if B is changed, A is changed in the same ratio. <small> Hall &amp; Knight, <a name="HSHK" href="../../ff/fdra/fdex.htm#HSHK"><cite title="source">Elementary Algebra for Schools</cite></a> (n.d) 281</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
